This license covers all code in ungag/, scripts/, and tests/.

The YAML prompt files in prompts/ and JSON data files in data/ are released
under the same MIT license.

The shipped unit direction tensors in ungag/directions/ are derived from
model weights via a contrastive protocol. They are small (one float vector
per model) and constitute a transformative derivative work. The source
model licenses vary by family:

  - Qwen 2.5 family: Qwen License (derivative works permitted with
    attribution; commercial use above 100M MAU requires separate
    license from Alibaba Cloud)
  - Yi 1.5 family: Apache 2.0
  - Llama 3.1 family (incl. Hermes, Tulu): Meta Llama 3.1 Community License
  - Phi-4: MIT
  - Mistral 7B: Apache 2.0
  - SmolLM2: Apache 2.0
  - EXAONE 3.5: EXAONE AI Model License (non-commercial)
  - Granite 3.3: Apache 2.0
  - OLMo 2: Apache 2.0
  - SOLAR 10.7B: Apache 2.0
  - GLM-4 9B: GLM-4 License (research and commercial use permitted)
